commit_message: Results with equal weight can now be returned. Closes #10.
Increased variation in output for equivilant matches.

Terminal now handles KeyboardInterrupt and EOF from ctrl+c and ctrl+d
to end chat bot sessions.

This also fixes an issue where chatbot would reply after the exit()
command was issued. In addition the exit() command has been marked
for deprication in favor of using KeyboardInterrupt and EOF commands.

Chatterbot now stores information in a dictionary.

This change fixes a major issue with how the chatterbot functions.
Previously the chatterbot recorded the entire conversation including
its own responces. As a result it was corrupting its own output.

The chatterbot now stores only the responces entered by the user.

Fixed dictionary key selection in python 3.

Python 3 has a different behavior for dict.keys such that it now
returns a dict_keys object instead of a list. This replicated the
python 2x .keys functionality by making an explicit call to list.

Created database controller layer.

This change was made to allow the future creation of additional
database adapters. This change starts to make alterations that
will make it easier to connect different database types. The
future goal will be to have data move as specified in the
following outline:

Layer 1: ChatterBot
  - This layer interacts with users and apis. It handles a simple
api that allow responce data to be entered.

Layer 2: Storage Controller
  - This layer recieves raw text or json data from layer 1.
  - Here, raw data is converted into Statement objects.
  - Statement objects can be modified and passed to Layer 3.
  - Statement objects can also be retreived from Layer 3.

Layer 3: Database Adapter
  - The database adapter layer is an implementation of a
simple interface that specifies basic operations that are
required to use a type of database. These methods include
getting and writing data.

commit_message: Modified chatterbot to use statement objects return by the storage adapter.
Added training example.

Added Signature object.

A signature object has been added. In the future, a statement may
have multiple signatures. Each signature will contain the name of
the user who said it, the date on which it was said, and any other
useful meta-data which may be required.

For now, statement objects still maintain the legacy name and date
fields. These two attributes will be removed in the future in favor
of the signature object.
Removed name and date attribute from statements.
Improved comments in examples.
Added tests for training and adapters.

Added json adapter and removed get_response_data method.

This change was done in favor of using the more flexable adapter
system to manage what the output format of the response is. This
change also simplifies the ChatterBot interface and removes a
redundant method call from get_response to get_response_data.
Added filter method to jsondb adapter.
Replaced helper method with filter.
Created additional methods for selecting a response statement.

commit_message:
Statement object list is now passed to logic adapters.

This makes it possible to create logic adapters that
use additional meta data from statements to select
a response.

Logic adapters now return statement object.

Since the list of statement objects is now passed to the logic
adapter, have the logic adapter return the matching statement
instead of doing another lookup.
Updated get_most_frequent_response to use the new response object format.
Response lists and occurence counts now increment correctly.

Corrected issue with empty string being passed in as input.

This was due to an issue in a dependency where the empty string
was being evaluated as false. The minimum required value of jsondb
bas been set to prevent this in the future.
Updated mongo adapter for new resposne structure.

Moved signatures to the response object.

Signatures are not used yet. In the future they will be used to
hold meta data about a response, such as who said it.
Updated version.

Removed GitHub io adapter.

This adapter was added as a test a while back and will not work
with the latest configuration of chatterbot. It is likely that
there will not be a GitHub io adapter in the future.
Renamed json adapter to avoid naming conflict when importing json.
Kwargs are now passed to io adapter.
Kwargs now passed to logic adapters
Updated required nltk version.

Modified importer so that cwd will not be changed.

Also removed a stray test database that made it's way into a commit.
readme fix

Modified base test case to remove all test data files.

Previously, if tests failed, randomly named test databases could
be left behind. This change makes it so that all test data files
are created within a directory which is created and removed after
tests have finished. In the case on an exception, a directory is
easier to manually clean up than many data files.

Corrected issues with loading data from corpus module.

Previously, corpus data modules were being treated as python modules.
This caused some strange issues with relative imports.
The problem has been fixed by redesigning the corpus loader to use
a data directory and traverse subdirectories to load any data files
contained within.
Added corpus data files so they will be included in packaged release.
Updated readme & release version.
Added corpus data to MANIFEST.in

Changed requirement for requests to compatible

Compatible allows automatic security updating without fear of breakage.
Used no output adapter for test cases to prevent data from being printed in test output.

Update examples

- Create two NoOutputAdapter examples, each using a different logic
adapter to demonstrate how to edit the settings for a ChatBot & to
demonstrate use of the NoOutputAdapter
- Updated terminal_example database location. Previously, it was
hardcoded to @gunthercox machine
Added not filter to jsondatabase adapter.

Added check to filter out any statements that do not have another
statement that lists them in the in_response_to field.

This change prevents random responses from being returned when the
closest match to the input statement is not a response of any known
statement.
Added trivia corpus.

Removed not filter.

This filter extension is not needed anywhere. Im removing it to
keep the code base clean, manageable and readable.
Organized some of the general chatterbot test cases.
Updated previously skipped test.
Switched to prefered os.path.join method.

Logic adapters should raise an exception if a list of options in not provided.

This adds a new exception class to be used in these cases.
The reason for making this change is because previously,
logic adapters returned the input statement in the case that
the list of possible options is empty. This gives a false
positive that an exact match to the statement exists in the
list. Instead, an exception should be thrown.

Copied statement list before loop to prevent errors.

The list is now copied before looping over the list because
random errors were occuring previously. It appears that these
errors were caused by modifying the list while iterating over it.

Each adapter can now reference other adapter types.

This addition makes changes so that adapters can take other adapters
as a parameter. The reason for this change is because it is needed
for logic adapters. Logic adapters should be able to access the
storage adapter to retrieve information. It is more efficient to
allow logic adapters direct access to the database than it is to
pass in a list of known statements as is currently done. With this
in mind, I have given all adapters access to each other to keep
the interfaces unified and easy to work with.

commit_message:
Changed input/output parameter requirements.

ChatterBot now requires a list of input and output adapter pairs
to be provided. Any number of pairs can be added, and each pair
must be a tuple containing only two elements. The first element
must be the dot notated import path to an input adapter and the
second element must be the dot notated import path to an output
adapter.

Removed get_input method.

This method was only used sometimes. It has been removed in favor
of doing things right and having the input adapter always be in
charge of where the input comes from.

Changed input and output parameter requirements.

ChatterBot now requires just one input adapter and output adapter
as parameters.

Removed weather logic adapter.

The weather logic adapter has a new home:
https://github.com/gunthercox/chatterbot-weather

It was removed from the main chatterbot project
to keep the number of requirements low. On top
of that, the weather logic adapter was also
completely untested, undocumented, and contained
multiple TODOs. In order to keep the quality of
chatterbot's software as high as possible this
adapter had to be pruned.

In the future it will be possible to download
the new chatterbot-weather module from PyPi.

commit_message: Use update instead of replace

Modify synset_distance comparison function

This makes changes to the function so that
it will return a percent of similarity
between the two statements it takes as
parameters. By returning a percent it
makes the output of this function easier to
compare to the output of other comparison
functions.
Specify decimals to help Python 2.x

Move matching logic adapter methods to parent class

The closest match adapter and closest meaning adapter
share very similar code that can now be combined into
the parent class that they both share.

In the future, the two subclasses will be removed in
favor of just setting the comparison_function parameter.
Improve value of maximum similarity

Move sentiment matching to it's own function

This allows the sentiment matching adapter to
be simplified.
Don't overide get method on ApproximateSentenceMatchAdapter

This adds a backwards compatable method
for setting parameters for specific adapters.

list for system logic adapters that are required to be present

Disconnect storage from adapter class

This makes a change to seperate the storage adapter from the base
Adapter class. This is being done because the methods on the base
Adapter class are not needed on the storage adapter.

The main change is that is no longer possible for the storage
adapter to access the ChatBot instance. This should not cause
any probems because there are no "known" use cases where this
is needed.

This also allows a special case to be removed in the class
validation utility so that a check to the "Adapter" class
is never made. This allows the class validation utility to
be more generic.

This fixes a bug with the assignment of the filters attribute, whereby a
generator, rather than it's result is assigned to the ChatBot.filters

commit_message:
Move relational fields out of abstract base models

ChatterBot's abstract base models for Django are suppose to make
it easier for a developer to create a new model, based on the
existing ones with their own modifications.

Unfortunately, having related fields like foregin keys will result
in errors when trying to create new models because the fields of
the abstract parent class are still evaluated by Django and
because they can only reference the origional models.

Revert "Move relational fields out of abstract base models"

Decrease the time complexity of ChatterBot corpus trainer

This is made more efficient by getting all of the data file paths
before training from them.

cleanup and removes tests and functionality for the read_only
parameter since that is no longer a function on the other two
storage adapters.

fix #1460

Objects have a better ability to be optomized for better memory
and processing usage than dictionaries do.

Try locking issues after 300 days instead of 365

This will hopefully help reduce the the number of commends left on old closed tickets. (It becomes difficult to keep track of these comments since the ticket has been closed and many times the commends are not relevant in relation to the original issue. It is probably better for new issues to have their own tickets.)

Remove pymongo from main dependency list

Pymongo isn't required unless the Mongo DB storage adapter is being
used. By not installing pymongo automatically, the installation
footprint of ChatterBot is decreased in size, which can be useful
when installing on devices that have limited storage space.
